  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "banxKj1zqUysCh9FhPzzGYTefD4=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:32.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "Because document models are event-sourced, changing a schema would break existing documents. Versioning solves this with four components:\n\n1. **Version Folders** - Separate `v1/`, `v2/` directories with version-specific gen/ and src/ code\n2. **DocumentModelModule** - Each version exports a module with an explicit `version` number\n3. **Upgrade Manifest** - Declares supported versions and upgrade paths for a document type\n4. **Upgrade Reducer** - Pure function that transforms document state from one version to another\n\nKey rules:\n- V1 documents continue to work with v1 reducers\n- New documents are created at the latest version by default\n- Upgrade reducers must handle both `state` and `initialState`\n- Never remove operations from newer versions\n- Don't change existing input schemas; add new operations instead\n- Upgrade reducers must be pure (no side effects)\n- Always provide sensible defaults for new fields\n- Never lose data during upgrades\n\nConnect and Switchboard automatically load all versions and upgrade manifests, handling version detection and migration transparently.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:32.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:32.000Z"
    }
  },
